ðŸ”§ Installs & Prerequisites
Before running this Terraform project, make sure the following tools are installed and configured on your local machine or cloud terminal:

âœ… 1. AWS CLI
Used to authenticate and manage AWS credentials.

Install:

bash
Copy
Edit
# macOS
brew install awscli

# Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt install awscli -y

# Windows (PowerShell)
choco install awscli
Configure your AWS credentials:

bash
Copy
Edit
aws configure
You'll be prompted for:

AWS Access Key ID

AWS Secret Access Key

Default region (e.g., us-east-1)

Output format (e.g., json)

âœ… 2. Terraform
The core tool used to define and provision infrastructure.

Install:

bash
Copy
Edit
# macOS
brew tap hashicorp/tap
brew install hashicorp/tap/terraform

# Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y gnupg software-properties-common curl
curl -fsSL https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg
echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg] https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com $(lsb_release -cs) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/hashicorp.list
sudo apt update && sudo apt install terraform

# Windows (PowerShell)
choco install terraform
Verify install:

bash
Copy
Edit
terraform -version
âœ… 3. SSH Key Pair
Youâ€™ll need a valid AWS EC2 key pair for SSH access to the deployed instance.

Create one in AWS Console or locally:

bash
Copy
Edit
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f my-key
Upload the .pem or .pub file to AWS â†’ EC2 â†’ Key Pairs.

Update the Terraform variable key_name in variables.tf with the name of your key.

